laboratory_examinations.findings: Visualized lung bases clear. Liver enhances homogeneously without focal lesions or intrahepatic biliary ductal dilatation. The portal vein is patent. Gallbladder unremarkable. A small splenule inferior to the main spleen noted. Kidneys present symmetric nephrograms and excretion of contrast without focal solid or cystic lesions. Mid to distal appendix thickened with hyperemia and minimal surrounding stranding, diameter measures 1.0 cm, no evidence of perforation. Minimal amount of surrounding fluid with tracking into the pelvis. Other abdominal structures and the bladder, prostate, and rectum are unremarkable.
